title: Elaine Chao
deleted: Following the [[2021 storming of the United States Capitol]], Chao submitted her resignation as Secretary of Transportation on January 7, 2021, in protest of President Trump's handling of what she described as a "traumatic and entirely avoidable event."<ref>{{cite news|last=Johnson|first=Ted|date=7 January 2021|title=Transportation Secretary Elaine Chao Resigns, Calls Siege Of Capitol "Entirely Avoidable"|url=https://www.yahoo.com/entertainment/transportation-secretary-elaine-chao-resigns-185105209.html|work=Yahoo|access-date=7 January 2021}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=McEvoy|first=Jemima|date=7 January 2021|title=Transportation Secretary Elaine Chao Resigns Over 'Traumatic' Capitol Attack|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jemimamcevoy/2021/01/07/transportation-secretary-secretary-chao-resigns-over-capitol-attack/?sh=1a1ceefa44b3|work=Forbes|access-date=7 January 2021}}</ref> Her resignation took effect on January 11, nine days before her term would have ended.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cnn.com/2021/01/07/politics/elaine-chao-cabinet-resignation-trump/index.html|title=Elaine Chao resigns as transportation secretary in wake of riot|first=Kaitlan|last=Collins|first2=Jeremy |last2=Diamond|work=CNN|date=January 7, 2021|accessdate=January 7, 2021}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |last=Rehman |first=Fareeha |date=2021-01-07 |title=Elaine Chao first Trump Cabinet member to resign after Capitol riot |language=en-US |work=KRON4 |url=https://www.kron4.com/news/national/elaine-chao-first-trump-cabinet-member-to-resign-after-capitol-riot/ |access-date=2021-01-07}}</ref>
